articles.title: About repository languages
articles.content: The files and directories within a repository determine the languages that make up the repository. You can view a repository's languages to get a quick overview of the repository. GitHub uses the open source Linguist library to determine file languages for syntax highlighting and repository statistics. Language statistics will update after you push changes to your default branch (which is usually master). Some files are hard to identify, and sometimes projects contain more library and vendor files than their primary code. If you're receiving incorrect results, please consult the Linguist troubleshooting guide for help.
